<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-4269] Connection to sftp server occasionally don&apos;t want to come back</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4269</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Problem appear if somebody kill logged on user on sftp server while you are connected with consumer.&lt;br/&gt;
Camel is not able to reconnect on next poll even if it says that it will do this.&lt;br/&gt;
RemoteFileConsumer is not connected but it thinks that it is still logged in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think &quot;loggedIn&quot; flag should be down after each disconnecting action like in attached patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
